<doc id="1107763" wikidata="Q1725198" url="?curid=1107763" title="Canton of Douvrin">
<text>The Canton of Douvrin is one of the cantons of the arrondissement of Béthune, in the Pas-de-Calais department, in northern France. Its seat is the town Douvrin.

==Composition==
At the French canton reorganisation which came into effect in March 2015, the canton was expanded from 5 to 14 communes:

*Annequin
*Auchy-les-Mines
*Billy-Berclau
*Cambrin
*Cuinchy
*Douvrin
*Festubert
*Givenchy-lès-la-Bassée
*Haisnes
*Lorgies
*Noyelles-lès-Vermelles
*Sailly-Labourse
*Vermelles
*Violaines 
